We recommended Management to require the:

Inventory Committee to conduct and prepare report on the Physical Count of Road Network of the municipality;


GSO-Designate to prepare and submit RLRN, maintain LRI, Road Map, and keep LRNPC for all roads and its components;


Office-in-Charge (OIC) – Municipal Engineer to provide the GSO-Designate and MA a report on the complete description and cost segregation of road components for road projects, with consideration to road intersections; and


Municipal Accountant to update the general ledger of the road network of the Municipality, prepare lapsing schedule for the depreciation and comply with the disclosure requirements for road network system in compliance to COA Circular No. 2015-005 dated November 23, 2015, in order to present fairly the FS of the Municipality.

We recommended Management:

Require the Municipal Accountant to reconcile the submitted RPCPPРЕ with that of accounting records and update PPE ledger cards in the course of reconciliation; 


Instruct the Inventory Committee to conduct physical inventory of the remaining properties and prepared the report thereon to be submitted to accounting office for reconciliation to ensure the existence, condition and accountability of the recorded PPEs balances are established: 

Instruct the GSO Designate to continue updating the property cards with details aligned with the inventory tag and renew the issuance of updated PAR/ICS to accountable officers;

For the unserviceable properties, to require the GSO Designate to segregate the properties for disposal through the execution of IIRUP, then instruct the Disposal/Inventory Committee to initiate the course of action to facilitate the disposal of properties to avoid further deterioration and reduction of value; and instruct the Municipal Accountant to make the necessary adjusting entries in the books upon disposal of said properties; and 

e. Exhaust all diligent efforts to account the non-existing properties by following the disposition procedures provided in Section 7 of COA Circular No. 2020-006.

