Municipal Accountant to update the general ledger of the road network of the Municipality as mandated by COA Circular No. 2015-005 dated November 23, 2015 and prepare the necessary lapsing schedule thereof, in order to fairly present all affected accounts in the financial statements.

require the GSO-Designate to religiously prepare RIS for all issuances of supplies and materials, consolidate the aforementioned forms to be attached in the preparation of SSMI and subsequently submit the reports to the Accounting Unit;

instruct the Municipal Accountant to prepare the necessary JEVs to record actual issuances, based on the submitted SSMI and RIS, and reflect issuances to its respective inventory accounts; and

require both the GSO and Accounting Office to consistently reconcile actual inventories on stock and inventory accounting records in order to achieve the computation of accurate balances and the timely discovery and correction of errors.

