We recommended Management to require the:
Inventory Committee to conduct and prepare report on the Physical Count of Road Network of the municipality;
GSO-Designate to prepare and submit RLRN, maintain LRI, Road Map, and keep LRNPC for all roads and its components;
Office-in-Charge (OIC) – Municipal Engineer to provide the GSO-Designate and MA a report on the complete description and cost segregation of road components for road projects, with consideration to road intersections; and
MA to update the general ledger of the road network of the Municipality, prepare lapsing schedule for the depreciation and comply with the disclosure requirements for road network system in compliance to COA Circular No. 2015-005 dated November 23, 2015, in order to present fairly the FS of the Municipality.

The noted deficiencies on the Accounts Payable year-end balance due to (1) misclassified accounts worth P4,560,771.38; (2) improperly set-up payables without valid claims P3,276,902.93; (3) failure to ever dormant accounts worth P1.408.411.35; (4) unidentified balances as well as existence of negative subsidiary ledger balances amounting to P317,890.16 and P672,868.75, respectively; and (5) failure to withheld taxes of the recorded payables for expenses and assets, which is not in adherence to the IPSAS 1, COA Circular No. 2015-009 dated December 1, 2015, Section 98 PD No. 1445 and BIR RMC No. 10-2018, affected management assertions on validity and accuracy, thus the account balance in the financial statements was not fairly presented.

We recommended that Management instruct the Municipal Accountant to: 

make the necessary adjustments on misclassified accounts and improperly recorded accounts payable without valid proof with aggregate amount of P8,049,282.31 to arrive at the correct balances of the affected accounts; 

observe proper accounting treatment and use of appropriate accounts to fairly present balances; 

evaluate the propriety of recorded accounts payable and consider the existence of supporting documents and/or proofs of actual delivery of goods and services;

verify validity of the payables aged over two years and send confirmation letters with identified creditors/claimants. Valid claims shall be paid, otherwise, cause the reversion of the payables to the unappropriated surplus; 

exert effort in retrieving the documents of unidentified payables and analyze the negative balances and make the necessary adjustments thereof;

Strictly comply with the timely withholding of taxes and effect the adjusting entries to recognize the withholding taxes portion of Accounts Payable.

We recommended that Management:

Provide enough storage space wherein unserviceable properties could be properly secured and safeguarded against the elements and instruct all offices to surrender their reported unserviceable properties in preparation for their ultimate disposal;

Direct the GSO Designate to finalize the Inspection and Inventory Report of Unserviceable Property (IIRUP) as basis in recording the dropping from the books the unserviceable properties carried in the PPE accounts; 



Direct the Appraisal and Disposal Committee to evaluate the reasonable appraisal value of the unserviceable properties listed in the IIRUP and promptly cause the disposal of these properties; and



Advise the personnel concerned to submit the IIRUP to the Accounting Office upon completion of the disposal activity as it will be the basis for adjusting the balances of the affected PPE accounts.

We recommended the following to the Management:

Exert extra effort in collecting the funds lent out by sending demand letters to concerned persons so other bona fide beneficiaries within the municipality could also avail of the program;




Draft the needed guidelines to enforce collection;





The Accounting Office is advised to trace from the related documents to identify the name of the beneficiaries of the various capital assistance; and





Reclassify the unliquidated cash advances from Other Receivables to Due from Officers and Employees to present fairly the financial statements.

